    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I tried to write a proper test for react-native, simple rendering. But it works while it should not (createElement('View') is not failing). It seems to be a jest issue, in jest, this works perfectly (with the native preset):\r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport 'react-native';\r\nimport React from 'react';\r\n\r\nimport renderer from 'react-test-renderer';\r\n\r\nit('renders correctly', () => {\r\n  const Root = 'View';\r\n  const App = () => <Root/>;\r\n\r\n  const tree = renderer.create(\r\n    <App />\r\n  ).toJSON();\r\n  expect(tree).toMatchSnapshot();\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nsee https://github.com/facebook/jest/issues/2283",
